      "id": "92df30f8_73d3a2c5",
      "file_path": "common/onap-generic-artifact-browser/onap-generic-artifact-browser-service/src/main/java/org/onap/sdc/gab/yaml/YamlParser.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 179,
      "message": "I dont see a point in this case to call available method. According to J doc:\n> 'Note that while some implementations of InputStream will return the total number of bytes in the stream, many will not. It is never correct to use the return value of this method to allocate a buffer intended to hold all data in this stream.\nA subclass' implementation of this method may choose to throw an IOException if this input stream has been closed by invoking the close() method.'\n\nIn total - IOException can be thrown from available method as well as from close() (assuming that stream would be already closed).\n\nNull-check is necessary to avoid null pointers as it still could be not initialized.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3663,
        "name": "Tomasz Golabek",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "tomasz.golabek@nokia.com",
        "username": "golabek"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-29 10:53:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "21810831_660cbb53",
      "unresolved": false
    },
